The paper deals with the problem of detecting adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves meta-learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and has been applied to various problems in computer vision and natural language processing. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing methods, which is related to the field of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the proposed method involves training a double-network framework, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
